title: 5.5.3 - Glaciers
section 5_5_3

  |Since {cite.1.'IPCC_2007 AR4} new and improved chronologies of {Glossary.*Glacier glacier} size variations were published. There is high confidence that glaciers at times have been smaller than at the end of the 20th century in many regions, but the precise glacier extent in the previous warm periods of the {Glossary.*Holocene Holocene} is often difficult to assess.


  

